reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good little projector
reviews.reviewText: I was actual pretty impressed with how easy this projector was to get set up and operate, and the quality of the video, especially for the price. It definitely needs to be dark or dusk at the very least if intending to use this outside though. It connected easily to both our fire TV stick and our Bluetooth speaker. We got it for our sons' outdoor movie party and it definitely exceeded our expectations and helped make the party a hit!

reviews.reviewText: If you only need 1080p, this will do the job. The ui isnt the greatest, but at this price cant ask too much. One warning though, it would turn itself on after a while and it gets very hot, recommended that you keep it unplugged when not using!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality for a low price
reviews.reviewText: We have a really small bedroom and I didn't want to mount a tv to the wall or take up space with a stand. I looked for a long time at different projectors comparing quality features and price. I ended up settling on this one. It is the perfect solution for us! The quality really is good. (I mean it's not 4k but let's be realistic in our hopes here lol) it offers multiple ways to set up the projection, behind screen, direct projection, different mounted positions as well. You can see some of the feature options in my photos including a direct cast from your phone to the device meaning no extra items to connect. Of course It does have HDMI and USB ports if you need to hook things up. The clarity of the image was decent. I am definitely satisfied with this projector. The sound that comes directly from it is also acceptable. It is pretty loud on it's own which if I use it with my camp equipment that's great because I don't have to connect speakers but at home it connects via Bluetooth right to my sound bar. In all the price in combination with all the features and the fact that it was basically barely more than plug and play, this projector was the best combination of value!
